cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with natural language generation and summarization, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of neural abstractive models and attention mechanisms suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The evaluation metrics used, such as perplexity and ROUGE scores, indicate a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the use of long sequences and scalability suggests a potential focus on neural networks (cs.NE).
